This paper proposes a framework for the functional analysis of telecommunication networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of graph theory metrics to recognize complex organizations, which is related to the field of social networks (cs.SI). The study of the relationship between functional complexity, robustness, and response to changes falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the implementation and outcome of a network function, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and cybersecurity (cs.CR).
